The paper focuses on functional grasp synthesis for anthropomorphic hands, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The authors also use a dataset of contact demonstrations, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for object recognition and tracking. The framework also involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG) for grasp synthesis. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of human-robot interaction, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
